article.description: — Jayden Saddler had 13 points and his three-point play with one second to go lifted Southern past Alabama A&M 50-49 on Saturday.
article.headline: Saddler's clutch play lifts Southern past Alabama A&M 50-49
article.linkText: Saddler's clutch play lifts Southern past Alabama A&M 50-49
article.story: NORMAL, Ala. -- — Jayden Saddler had 13 points and his three-point play with one second to go lifted Southern past Alabama A&M 50-49 on Saturday. Tyrone Lyons added 12 points for the Jaguars, who held the Bulldogs to 28.3 percent shooting, the lowest mark of the season for a Southern opponent. Terrell Williams had eight rebounds for Southern (17-13, 11-6 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Jalen Johnson had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Bulldogs (11-17, 10-8), whose six-game winning streak was snapped. Garrett Hicks added 12 points and eight rebounds. The Jaguars improved to 2-0 against the Bulldogs on the season. Southern defeated Alabama A&M 73-64 on Feb. 5. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
